      "check": {
        "type": "identity",
        "lhs": "sin(t)**2 + cos(t)**2",
        "rhs": "1"
      },
      "steps": [
        {"text": "In a right-angled triangle with hypotenuse h, opposite side a and adjacent side b, the Pythagoras theorem gives a^2 + b^2 = h^2.", "latex": "a^2 + b^2 = h^2"},
        {"text": "Divide both sides by h^2.", "latex": "\\left(\\tfrac{a}{h}\\right)^2 + \\left(\\tfrac{b}{h}\\right)^2 = 1"},
        {"text": "By definition a/h = sin(theta) and b/h = cos(theta), giving the fundamental identity.", "latex": "\\sin^2\\theta + \\cos^2\\theta = 1"}
      ]
